The author expresses their best wishes to Archbishop Desmond Tutu on his 90th birthday and celebrates his contributions to humanity. They have had the honor of meeting him several times and admire his commitment to human rights and speaking out for what is right. Archbishop Tutu became known for challenging the injustice of Apartheid in South Africa, which inspired the author's own commitment to changing American policy towards the regime. His message of justice, equality, and reconciliation continues to inspire people worldwide. The author calls on everyone to recommit themselves to the work that has animated Archbishop Tutu's life, including advancing respect for human rights, strengthening equality, protecting fundamental freedoms, and fighting for racial justice.